The Mouse Who Woke Up For Christmas

by Luke A. Jones

You are in a Garden Shed.

You groggily awake from your hibernation to the deafening sound of your alarm clock. Better switch it off quick before it attracts attention.

You can see a Bed (containing Jessica), a Fireplace, a Wardrobe, a Toolbox, a Mantelpiece, an Alarm Clock, a Mirror, a Stocking, a Fridge and a Photo Frame.

You can go out.

> switch off clock

> switch off clock

You bring your paw down on top of the alarm clock and switch it off. The sudden silence is as deafening as the alarm itself.

Now you can think clearly you remember why you set the alarm. It was so that Jessica (your daughter) could see Christmas Day for the first time. She refused go into hibernation until you promised to wake her up. She's as stubborn as her mother, so you had to agree.

It's Christmas Eve morning, so plenty of time to gather the things you will need. Light a fire, find some food, find a stocking and hang it up,  find a present to give to Jessica and some beer for yourself.

You write a list on the back of a scrap of paper and put it in your pocket.
> x me

> x me

A distinguished gentleman mouse named Gerald. You have light tan fur, long whiskers and a pink tail.

You are wearing a pair of  Long Johns and a pair of pyjamas and slippers.
> i

> i
You are carrying a pair of  Long Johns (worn), a pair of pyjamas and slippers (worn) and a To Do List.
> x list

> x list
1. Light the fireplace.
2. Hang up Jessica's stocking on the mantelpiece.
3. Find a present for Jessica (and put it inside her stocking).
4. Buy some beer for yourself.
> x johns

> x johns

A pair of white woollen long johns.
> x pyjamas

> x pyjamas
Your sleeping attire consisting of a rather fetching red silk pyjama shirt, trousers, nightcap and a pair of slippers, with a fleur-de-lis pattern in black.

The label inside the pyjama's reads;

'Elite Couture'
handmade by P.Spider.
> x slippers

> x slippers

A pair of Persian slippers in gold and black leather. They curl up at the toes in an Aladdin style.
> x Jessica

> x Jessica

Your precious daughter Jessica. She lies soundly asleep, her snow-white and grey flecked fur rises and falls as she breathes. In her paw you can see that she is gripping a note, you gently prise it from her. It is a note addressed to Santa.
> x note

> x note
In Jessica's unsteady infant writing it reads:

A pang of hurt stabs at your chest, your wife Gemma went missing last summer, when it was so dry she left the garden to try and find water.

She never returned, and to add salt to the wound the weather broke that night in huge thunderstorm.

You held Jessica all night until she eventually cried herself to sleep.
> x bed

> x bed
A mouse sized four-poster bed with a crib attached at the bottom.
 In which there is Jessica.
> x crib

> x crib
A wooden crib attached to the foot of the bed, which Jessica sleeps in.
> x fireplace

> x fireplace

A fireplace fashioned out of an old tin can, with a carved wooden mantelpiece surround. There is a cylindrical metal chimney pipe which exits through a small hole in the shed wall.
> x mantelpiece

> x mantelpiece
A wooden mantelpiece surrounding the fire, a grapevine pattern is carved into it. The perfect place to hang up a stocking for Jessica (if you had a stocking and something to hang it up with).
> x pipe

> x pipe
A cylindrical metal pipe that acts as a chimney for the fireplace. It exits through a small hole in the shed wall.
> x hole

> x hole
A small hole in the wall of the shed, through which the chimney from the fireplace exits.
> x mirror

> x mirror

A full length (for a mouse) floor mirror with a wooden frame.

Looking into the mirror you see;

A distinguished gentleman mouse named Gerald. You have light tan fur, long whiskers and a pink tail.

You are wearing a pair of  Long Johns and a pair of pyjamas and slippers.
> x stocking

> x stocking

One of Jessica's knee-length socks, knitted by her mother.

It's ready to be hung up, but it looks like moths have been in the shed while you were asleep as it now has a large hole in the foot.
> x fridge

> x fridge

Your small white fridge, which is sadly devoid of beer.
> x frame

> x frame

A guilded photo frame with a polaroid photo of your family; your daughter Jessica, your wife Gemma and you.

It was taken last spring by your cousin Chris when he came to visit.
> x wardrobe

> x wardrobe
A Victorian, mahogany, two door, mouse sized wardrobe.
> open it

> open it
You open it.
It contains a Smart Suit and Gardening Clothes.
> x suit

> x suit

A sharply cut black silk suit consisting of  jacket, trousers, white shirt, waistcoat, black tie, and a pair of black leather brogues.

The label inside the suit reads;

'Elite Couture'
handmade by P.Spider.
> x clothes

> x clothes

Your gardening gear, consisting of black jeans, t-shirt, woolly jumper and a pair of rubber boots.
> remove pyjamas

> remove pyjamas
You take them off
> put pyjamas in wardrobe

> put pyjamas in wardrobe
Done.
> take clothes

> take clothes
You pick it up.
> wear clothes

> wear clothes
You put them on.
> x mirror

> x mirror

A full length (for a mouse) floor mirror with a wooden frame.

Looking into the mirror you see;

A distinguished gentleman mouse named Gerald. You have light tan fur, long whiskers and a pink tail.

You are wearing a pair of  Long Johns and Gardening Clothes.
> x jeans

> x jeans

A pair of black LeviTM  501's.
> x t-shirt

> x t-shirt

A jet black T-Shirt.
> x jumper

> x jumper

A thick white woolen jumper with a black nordic snowflake design. A present from your Swedish cousin Gustav.
> x boots

> x boots

A pair of Le Chameau Vierzon Rubber Boots, olive green in colour and leather lined.
> x toolbox

> x toolbox
A mouse sized Snap-OnTM toolbox, containing mouse sized equipment.
> open toolbox

> open toolbox
You open it.
It contains A Roll of Duct Tape, A Bottle of Firelighter Fluid  and an Oily Rag.
> x tape

> x tape
Very tough plastic tape with strong adhesive.
> x fluid

> x fluid

A bottle of lighter fluid (easier to carry than heavier fluid).

It gives off a heady greasy alcohol smell.
> x rag

> x rag

A yellow rag soaked in oily polish.
> out

> out

You are at the Bottom of the Garden.

It is cold enough that you can see your breath in the air.

You can see a Barbecue, a Bird Skull and a Garden Shed.

You can go south, east, northeast, in or up.

> x barbecue

> x barbecue
A kettle barbecue belonging to the human owner of the house, it towers above you.
> x skull

> x skull
The calcified remains of a bird's skull. Judging by the thickness and strength of the beak it probably belonged to a member of the corvid family.
> x shed

> x shed

The garden shed where you live.

It's a bit rickety, and could do with a lick of paint, but it's cosy and it's home.
> ne

> ne

Brandishing your Rubber Boots you enter the Vegetable Patch.

You are in the Vegetable Patch.

As you enter the vegetable patch you hear the patio door open. You quickly hide behind the wheelbarrow.

A human comes out of the house, walks over to the vegetable patch, digs a hole with the spade and picks up a potato from the ground. They disappear back into the house and you hear the patio door clunk shut again.

As you emerge from behind the wheelbarrow you hear a loud bang in the distance.

You can see a Spade, a Hole, Stewart the Snail, a Large Stone and a Wheelbarrow.

You can go south, east, southeast, southwest or northwest.

> x spade

> x spade
Nothing out of the ordinary.
> x hole

> x hole

A muddy hole that you saw the human dig.
It contains a Coin.
> x coin

> x coin
A small sliver coloured coin, perhaps the human dropped it. It is dull and tarnished.
> x Stewart

> x Stewart

You stare at the snail, but you can't make out any of its features as the author of this game hasn't worked this NPC out yet.
> talk to Stewart

> talk to Stewart

"I'm a NPC that hasn't been programmed yet, I hope you are having a nice time."
> x stone

> x stone
A large stone with a gritty texture.
> x wheelbarrow

> x wheelbarrow
An old wooden wheelbarrow with traces of ancient green paint that has flaked away to almost nothing.
> nw

> nw

You are Behind The Shed.

An overgrown and neglected part of the garden.

It is damp as well as cold here.

You can see a Compost Heap (containing a Cricket Ball), a Pallet, Nail and a Match.

You can go southeast.

> x pallet

> x pallet
An old broken wooden pallet, there is a nail sticking out of it on one side.
> x nail

> x nail
A small steel nail sticking slightly out of the pallet of wood.
> take nail

> take nail
It is stuck firmly into the pallet.
> x match

> x match

A non-safety match with a red head.
> x heap

> x heap

An old compost heap, it is giving off a bit of heat and wisps of vapour as it decomposes.
It contains a Cricket Ball.
> x ball

> x ball

An old faded and battered cricket ball with a stitched seam.

It is so heavy that if you want to take it you'll have to drop everything else you are carrying (except for clothes and your To Do List).
> take ball

> take ball
You pick it up.
> se

> se

Brandishing your Rubber Boots you enter the Vegetable Patch.

You are in the Vegetable Patch.

The human who lives in the house is a keen gardener.

In the spring and summer there are wonderful beans and courgettes, followed by luscious cabbages and other assorted brassicas.

You try to not steal too many through the year, but you get the impression that the human doesn't mind too much anyway, he feeds the birds and even the squirrels.

Now in midwinter it is a bare and muddy patch of earth.

You can see a Spade, a Hole (containing a Coin), Stewart the Snail, a Large Stone and a Wheelbarrow.

You can go south, east, southeast, southwest or northwest.

> sw

> sw

You are at the Bottom of the Garden.

It is cold enough that you can see your breath in the air.

You can see a Barbecue, a Bird Skull and a Garden Shed.

You can go south, east, northeast, in or up.

> s

> s

You are are Under the Tree.

You are underneath the tall cherry tree. You can hear thumping bass coming from inside the Squirrel Midden.

A rather vicious looking Weasel is guarding the entrance.

You can see an Entrance to the Squirrel Midden, a Tree and a Weasel.

You can go north, northeast, up or in.

> x weasel

> x weasel

A Weasel dressed up as a nightclub bouncer. He is wearing a black suit with a white shirt and black tie.

Even though it is midwinter he is wearing dark sunglasses.

In his ear you can see make out an earpiece with a curly wire which disappears somewhere underneath his jacket.

He is armed with a Machete which he grips in one paw.

His face is heavily scarred.

> x machete

> x machete

A long and lethal looking machete.
> x tree

> x tree

A tall cherry tree, bare of leaves as it is winter.

There is an old carving in the bark; a heart with an arrow through it.

Inside the heart is carved:

G.M.
 4
G.M.
I.D.S.T.

> x midden

> x midden
The entrance to the Squirrel Midden is guarded by a Weasel.

Above the entrance is a flickering neon sign that reads 'The Nutcracker Club'.
> talk to weasel

> talk to weasel

 "Sorry Sir, I can't really talk while on duty" says the Weasel
> in

> in

You try to go past the Weasel, but he steps into your path.

"Sorry Sir, you can't come in wearing that. Club rules!"
> u

> u
You scramble up the tree. The bark is gnarly, twisted, and easy to grip onto.

You are at the a Top of the Tree.

You can see Peter Magpie and a Collection of Shiny Things.

You can go down.

> x Peter

> x Peter
A black and white magpie called Peter.

He is currently adjusting the arrangement of his shiny things.
> x shiny

> x shiny
A magpie cache. Peter is obsessed with shiny things and guards them jealously.
It contains some Rings, a Metal Bar and Half of a metal watch strap.
> x rings

> x rings

A collection of various silver and gold rings.
> x bar

> x bar

A shiny silver metal bar.
> x strap

> x strap

A section of metal watch strap, judging by the distinctive linkage it was once part of a Tag Heur.
> talk to Peter

> talk to Peter

 "Hello Gerald, Have you seen any shiny things around the garden today?" says Peter.
> ask Peter about shiny

> ask Peter about shiny

"Oh do you like shiny things too?" says Peter, "I've been working on this collection for a couple of years now, the arrangement takes a lot of finessing."
> ask Peter about rings

> ask Peter about rings

"Nice aren't they!" says Peter

"A good selection of sizes and shapes, and so shiny!"
> ask Peter about strap

> ask Peter about strap

"I'm so pleased with it!" says Peter,

"I'd been looking for one for ages, but just couldn't find the time."
> put ball in collection

> put ball in collection

Peter hops over to the collection of shiny things,

"This isn't shiny!" says Peter and pushes the Cricket Ball over the side of the tree.

Below you hear a 'Bonk!' and a muffled yelp followed by a 'Thud!'
> take bar

> take bar

"Oi! That my shiny thing!" says Peter,

"I might let you have it if you can find something better to replace it with though. The feng shui isn't quite right with it."

Peter fusses and rearranges his shiny things.
> d

> d

You are are Under the Tree.

You are underneath the tall cherry tree. You can hear thumping bass coming from inside the Squirrel Midden.

A rather vicious looking Weasel is lying unconscious  near the entrance to a squirrel midden.

You can see an Entrance to the Squirrel Midden, a Tree, an Unconscious Weasel, a Cricket Ball and a Machete.

You can go north, northeast, up or in.

> x weasel

> x weasel

An unconscious and gently snoring Weasel dressed up as a nightclub bouncer.

He is wearing a black suit with a white shirt and black tie.

Even though it is midwinter he is wearing dark sunglasses.

In his ear you can see make out an earpiece with a curly wire which disappears somewhere underneath his jacket.

His face is heavily scarred.

Sticking out of the top pocket of his jacket is a flyer of some sort, you take it.
> x flyer

> x flyer

A flyer you took from the Weasel.

The flyer is advertising the Grand Opening of Petcetera, a new pet store opening on Boxing Day.

Scribbled on the back in biro it reads,

'Nick - 07505 457 1262'.
> take machete

> take machete

 You pick up the Weasel's machete, it is heavy, but perfectly balanced.

Gripping with both front paws you try out a few practise swings.
> in

> in

You step over the unconscious Weasel and enter the Squirrel Midden.

You are in The Nutcracker Night Club (Inside the Squirrel Midden).

